quran[36]{c,v,t}:
  56,39,A number from those in the past
  56,40,And a number from those of later times
  56,41,"The companions of the left hand, who will be the companions of the left hand"
  56,42,They will be in the middle of a fierce blast of fire and in boiling water
  56,43,And in the shades of black smoke
  56,44,"Nothing to refresh, or to please them"
  56,45,"Because they were accustomed to indulging, before that, with their wealth"
  56,46,And insisted on great harm
  56,47,"And they used to say, “What, when we die and become dust and bones, will we then indeed be raised up again"
  56,48,“And our ancestors?”
  56,49,"Say, “Yes, those in the past and those of later times"
  56,50,"“All will certainly be gathered together, for the meeting appointed for a day well-known"
  56,51,"“Then will you truly, O you who go wrong by treating truth as falsehood"
  56,52,“You will surely taste of the Tree of Zaqqum
  56,53,“Then and there you will fill your insides
  56,54,“And drink boiling water on top of it
  56,55,“Indeed you will drink like thirsty camels.”
  56,56,Such will be their entertainment on the Day of Punishment
  56,57,It is We Who have created you. Why will you not witness the truth
  56,58,Do you then see that which you throw out
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or are We the Creators"
  56,60,"We have decreed death for you, and We are not to be stopped–"
  56,61,"From changing your forms, and creating you in forms that you know not"
  56,62,And you certainly already know the first form of creation. Why then do you not praise Him
  56,63,Do you see the seed that you sow in the ground
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it to grow, or are We the cause"
  56,65,"Were it Our will, We could crumble it to dry powder, and you would be left in wonderment–"
  56,66,"Saying, “We are indeed left with debts"
  56,67,“Indeed we are shut out.”
  56,68,Do you see the water which you drink
  56,69,Do you bring it down from the cloud or do We
  56,70,"If it were Our will, We could make it salty. So why do you not give thanks"
  56,71,Do you see the fire which you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who causes the tree to grow which feeds the fire, or do We cause it to grow"
  56,73,"We have made it a memorial, an article of comfort, and convenience for the denizens of deserts"
  56,74,"Then glorify with praises the name of your Lord, the Supreme"